    1. Structure

Let's take a look at the enfusion://ResourceManager/~ArmaReforger:Prefabs/Vegetation/Core/Tree_Base.et Prefab to understand a `BaseContainer`'s structure:

```cpp
Tree {
 // ...
 Flags 524291
 MaxHealth 10000
 // ...
}
```

-  is the `BaseContainer`'s class
- there is no inheritance, this is the topmost Prefab; inheritance (e.g in enfusion://ResourceManager/~ArmaReforger:Prefabs/Vegetation/Tree/Tree_Coniferous_Base.et) looks like this:
```cpp
Tree : "{388AE316D09D0680}Prefabs/Vegetation/Core/Tree_Base.et" {
 // ...
}
```

    - `Tree` being the class (a Prefab can have a class that is different from its ancestor)
    - {{hl|"{388AE316D09D0680}Prefabs/Vegetation/Core/Tree_Base.et"}} being the ancestor, the inherited Prefab
- its `Flags` value is 524291, which is the `General > Flags` value of `Traceable`, `Visible` and `Relative Y` flags together
- its `MaxHealth` value is 10000, which is a GameCode-side property (not defined in script)

      1. Inheritance

In case of inheritance:
- every level can set a property's value
- if the value is not defined in a level, the value is read from its ancestor where it is defined (making it a "default value" for its children)
- if a property is not set anywhere, the default value is the type's default value (see Arma Reforger:Scripting: Values#Types)

